main event: Multiple observers reported sighting a bright, round object emitting a reddish-orange glow in Baker, Oregon on October 10, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for about three minutes before disappearing,All observers described the object as larger than a star or planet,The weather was clear at the time of the sighting,There was no known aircraft activity in the area when the object was detected,Photos of the sighting were taken but not included in the report.
sighted object: a bright, reddish-orange glowing elliptical object
witness description: Observers included civilians and military personnel with varying reliability levels.
